<title>USA: Republic Group sets gypsum plant expansion.</title>
<headline>Republic Group sets gypsum plant expansion.</headline>
<dateline>HUTCHINSON, Kan. 1997-02-20</dateline>
<text>
<p>Republic Group Inc said Thursday its Republic Gypsum Co subsidiary will expand and upgrade gypsum wallboard production through a $26 million plan at its facilities in Duke, Okla.</p>
<p>The project will take about 18 months to complete, Republic said. Funds will be supplied from the company's cash and investment balances.</p>
<p>About 15 percent of the company's recycled paperboard production output is used by its gypsum wallboard segment.</p>
<p>((--Chicago Newsdesk 312 408-8787))</p>
